<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUL 94 / Delays at Athens airport
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ATHENS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Greek Transport Minister Theodoros Pangalos warned summer travellers
yesterday that long delays at Athens airport would persist because of the
big seasonal increase in flights. The delays, often of two to four hours,
are due to air traffic controllers' refusal to work overtime, an inadequate
radar system and a 30 per cent increase in flights during the summer. Mr
Pangalos wants a new radar system operational as soon as possible but ruled
out a wage increase. The Board of Airlines Representatives said: 'The
situation is a nightmare for tourists and threatens Greece's commercial
interests.'
</TEXT>
