FT  14 JUL 94 / International Company News: International Paper improves in
second term
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
International Paper achieved earnings of Dollars 87m, or 70 cents a share in
the second quarter, up 13 per cent from Dollars 77m, or 62 cents, in the
same 1993 period, writes Laurie Morse.
The second quarter also showed improvement over this year's first quarter,
with rising paper and packaging prices boosting profits.
'This quarter's earnings performance reflects the pricing improvements
International Paper is now realising in most of our product lines,' chairman
Mr John Georges said.
Second-quarter sales rose to Dollars 3.6bn, from Dollars 3.5bn in the same
1993 quarter. The company said price increases for containerboard, pulp and
uncoated printing papers had held through the quarter.
