FT  14 JUL 94 / Observer: To the hilt
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bristol &amp; West Building Society is so concerned to take the public's views
into account that it commissioned research to find out what people wanted
from a mortgage. It found that the public was not seduced by the various
cashback schemes which have cluttered the market recently but looked at a
mortgage in terms of monthly payments. How wise of the society then to
launch a new range of mortgages on the basis of those findings; how sad,
however, for existing B&amp;W borrowers who find that the standard variable rate
they pay is - at 7.89 per cent - the highest charged by any of the ten
largest societies.
