FT  14 JUL 94 / Observer: Explosive stuff
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
While the world is exercised about the vaulting price of coffee, scant
attention has been afforded the recent surge in the price of methanol. This
key ingredient in methylated spirits was going for less than DM200 per tonne
last year; it now costs over DM550 per tonne.
Although it is best known as a cheap if unpalatable alternative to whisky,
meths is now an essential ingredient in unleaded petrol. Another sign that
the price of supermarket petrol may soon be heading in the same direction as
the price of supermarket coffee?
</TEXT>
