<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUL 94 / Truce agreed in glazing dispute
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A truce was agreed in the High Court yesterday in a poaching dispute between
Anglian Windows, the Norwich-based double-glazing company, and Aspen
Windows, set up by Mr George Williams, Anglian's founder and former chief.
Anglian, the UK's biggest double-glazing group, is suing Aspen, Mr Williams,
and 10 salesmen who left Anglian to join Aspen. It claims the 10 are in
breach of their contracts.
Pending a full hearing of the dispute, the salesmen gave undertakings to Mr
Justice Aldous not to solicit customers who were Anglian customers during
specified periods. Aspen pledged not to induce breaches of contract by the
10 or any other Anglian representatives.
</TEXT>
