<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUL 94 / Civil Service White Paper: Main points
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The creation of a new senior group within the civil service for about 3,000
top mandarins ranked at grade five and above
Top posts to be considered for open advertising, with more outsiders coming
in and encouragement for civil servants to seek outside experience
Personal contracts for senior civil servants, with more flexible pay
reflecting responsibilities and performance
Greater devolution of responsibility to Whitehall departments - including
for pay and grading
Civil service numbers to be cut to below 500,000 by 1998, with de-layering
at the top
An end to central targets on market-testing - departments to decide on how
to live within running costs freeze
</TEXT>
