<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUL 94 / World Cup '94: Goals bring joy to weary people
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In Brazil as elsewhere, the weary people need a glimpse of happiness. Goals
give them that. Recent research has shown that factory workers are much more
productive the day after a Brazilian victory. Should Brazil win the World
Cup, the country will close for at least one day of celebration. If it
loses, experts say, there will be an increase in suicides.
Brazilian players do not consider this a burden. They are protected by their
cockiness - so long as they do not lose. After Brazil's 3-2 quarter-final
win against Holland, Romario told reporters: 'You witnessed art today,'
while Brazil manager Carlos Alberto Parreira said: 'The last 34 minutes
provided some of the most exciting, dramatic moments of the World Cup.'
</TEXT>
