FT  14 JUL 94 / Riviera beach pollution claim
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NICE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Excessively high levels of bacteria from human waste were found in the water
off four of 11 French Riviera beaches tested, environmentalists said
yesterday. The Greens party called for an investigation on whether bathing
was safe at the four beaches after laboratory tests of water quality were
conducted at the request of the Vai Nissa, an association led by Patrice
Miran, a political leader in the region who is also a Greens member. The
tests, conducted last week, found levels of bacteria well above guidelines
set by the European Union. The areas found to be polluted were the Flots
Bleus beach at Saint-Laurent-du-Var, the Palais and Midi beaches at Cannes,
and an unidentified beach at Nice.
