FT  13 JUL 94 / International Company News: Forecast hits Goodyear shares
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Goodyear closed down at a 52-week low yesterday after the chairman
of the US tyre group forecast record second-quarter earnings of between
Dollars 158m and Dollars 164m, or between Dollars 1.05 and Dollars 1.09 a
share.
But the forecast results - which also represent a solid improvement on the
same quarter a year ago, when Goodyear earned Dollars 137.6m, or 95 cents a
share - were slightly lower than Wall Street had been expecting.
Industry analysts had forecast that Goodyear would report earnings of
between Dollars 1.10 and Dollars 1.15 a share in the quarter.
It was this disappointment which prompted some investors to sell Goodyear
shares yesterday. Earlier they had fallen as much as Dollars 2 to Dollars 34
3/4 but later rallied to close down Dollars 1 3/4 at Dollars 35.
Mr Stanley Gault, Goodyear's chairman, outlined the company's expectations
for the second quarter in a television interview. He said sales in the
period would be just over Dollars 3bn, marginally higher than a year ago.
Excluding revenues from previously divested assets, however, April-to-June
sales should set a record.
Mr Gault also said that demand for Goodyear products in North America was
strong, with plants running at near full-capacity, and that Latin American
and Asian operations should report strong performances. But the European
market was soft.
</TEXT>
