FT  13 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Davis agrees terms for Lakeland Pennine
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Davis Service Group, the business services company formerly known as Godfrey
Davis, yesterday announced that it had reached agreement on the terms of its
recommended offers for the acquisition of Lakeland Pennine Group.
The offers, which value Lakeland's share capital at Pounds 7.25m, are
conditional among other things on acceptances being received by not less
than 90 per cent of each class of Lakeland shares.
