2.33m and were achieved after costs incurred in the setting up of two new
brands, Mr Green stated.
The level of net bank borrowings continued to fall and was reduced from
Pounds 3.1m to Pounds 2.02m, resulting in gearing of 24.2 per cent (37 per
cent).
